				<td colspan="2"><span>I apologize if this has been brought up before.  I was just browsin' the different boards out there and I came across this (found <a target="_new" href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=beastlord&amp;message.id=3069&amp;no_redir=true"><u>here</u></a> ) that was posted on 9/23/04:
<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Coming to Test soon -
<br />
 
<br />
Your pets will stay with you even when you are invisible.  I am not sure when it's going to test server and then live but this is something Development is planning on doing.
<br />

<br />
Ashlanne Barefoot
<br />
Sony Online Entertainment
<br />
Bare Foot and Flame Resistant since 2000 </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
This issue has the potential of affecting swarm kiting.  It is somewhat hampered already for those 66+ if I understand it correctly.  If this change takes place it would practically eliminate the tactic across all levels.  Sure, dispell would still work, but not nearly as well as invis.
<br />

<br />
Of course, I'm just being a naysayer for now.  For all we know, this implementation may be a long way off, if ever.  Also, Ash doesn't alude to what type of pet (summoned, charmed) will be affected, so don't make any assumptions yet.  The above paragraph is just from a perspective of worse case scenerio.  I just thought it was an interesting enough tidbit of info to watch out for at least.  
<br />

<br />
  </span></td>
