				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Something to keep an eye out for...<a name="65741"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 5 04 8:40 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>For enchanter animations, I think SOE should consider making the &quot;Go Away&quot; command available when the invis change goes live. However, even if this doesn't happen, one can still use Reclaim Energy or get level 1 of the Animation Empathy AA (which allows the use of &quot;Go Away&quot;).
<br />

<br />
Since the invis change does NOT affect charmed pets at all (it is for summoned pets only), the current methods of breaking charm will still work just fine.
<br />

<br />
Using the &quot;Go Away&quot; command on summoned pets is like being able to click off your own beneficial buff at any time. Charm, however, is a detrimental spell on an enemy, and in my opinion it should not be removable via a command. As long as dispell/invis still work for breaking charm (which they will), I'm personally fine with not adding a &quot;Go Away&quot; command for charmed pets.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
