				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Charm, however, is a detrimental spell on an enemy, and in my opinion it should not be removable via a command</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
This is very true, but in reality if a Enchanter, Bard, Wiz or whatever was to cast a spell on you they should have the power to remove it. I think the go away command on charmed mobs even would be awesome. Less 1 spell slot for invis and it give you total control of the pet in a sense. You charm it you command it you should be able to break your hold on the being at will. It would also work that way on a chanter or bard mez. The chanter or bard at the time is holding you in a state of awe if you will. When he or she is ready for you to be awakened they should be able to pull the mez of you with out having to dispell you. 
<br />

<br />
I think the way SoE is going with all the odd new changes is they are testing out the play ability of EQ2. I think all the changes we are seeing of late are going to be apart of the new everquest, and this is just a easy way to test how it will effect everyone. </span></td>
